After playing EQ for over two years now I feel <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>exactly</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> this way Labbie.  Expecting Verant to listen to my every complaint and respond quickly to all my petitions is the fast track to disappointment and frustration.  And that's not a slur on Verant, it's just a statement of reality.  So if I'm going to stay here and enjoy myself then I need to assume some of the responsibility for identifying the things that are not worth hassling with (often done through experience) and making it my business to avoid them.  There are many quests etc. in the game that I'm not going to tackle because the reward doesn't justify the effort.  But for others with different values from mine they can be a major attraction.  Anyhoo there's plenty of fun stuff to do here and fun peeps to meet, all possible without any assistance from customer support personnel.  And when it all gets to be too much, I take a break and come back another time.<br>
